modules.description: This module implements numerical methods for finding maxima of univariate functions within specified intervals. It provides two algorithms: `brent` for general maximization on a closed interval and `golden_search` for cases where an intermediate point with a higher value is already known. These functions are used in optimization tasks where a single-variable function's maximum must be located efficiently within a bounded domain.

Implements Brent's method and golden section search for finding local minima of continuous functions on closed intervals. Operates on real-valued functions with floating-point inputs and outputs, requiring interval bounds and optional tolerance parameters. Useful for numerical optimization tasks in scientific computing and engineering applications.
